## Relation to Bodies of Knowledge:

The continuum also maps to which Bodies of Knowledge are emphasized:

    RT ────→ Theoretical CER (Phase 1)
    RD ────→ Experimental CER (Phase 2) + Applied CER (Phase 4)
    PT ────→ State of the Art (Phase 3) + Applied CER (Phase 4)
    PD ────→ Applied CER (Phase 4) + Educational Impact (Phase 5)


Embody's span (RT → RD → PT) means it contributes to:
    ✓ Theoretical CER (1.B domain-specific theories)
    ✓ Experimental CER (enabling 2.B experiments)
    ✓ State of the Art (3.A/B synthesis)
    ✓ Applied CER (4.A prototype)


