SUMMARY:
────────

The Research/Practice and Theory/Design continuum is a 2D space defining
contribution types. Embody spans from RT (research theories) through RD
(research designs) to PT (practice theories), exemplifying translational
work that bridges multiple positions simultaneously.

This spanning is not unusual—it's precisely what TCER Phase 4.A activities
in trading zones are designed to do: coordinate research and practice by
occupying multiple continuum positions.

